race.comment: CARBONADOS (3) turned up at Randwick fresh and quickened up really nicely. Won going away and the rating said that he was back better than ever. Unable to go on with that and a bit plain at Rosehill last time but they were back in a sit-sprint 1100m there and the return to 1200m can get him back on track. RECON (5) did a terrific job to keep the winning run going last time. Rallied and beat off a smart one who had the cold drop on him. ZOUPER FUND (9) keeps turning up and winning (four of his past five) and the clock backed up the fresh effort over a solid stablemate. CELSIUS STAR (4) backs up looking to strike while the iron is hot having landed a surprise win last week.
